@startuml
title ISL Glossary Platform - Django Prototype Structure

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false

actor "Browser user" as User

node "Django project" {
  component "isl_glossary_platform" as Project {
    [settings.py]
    [urls.py]
  }

  component "glossary app" as App {
    [models.py]
    [views.py]
    [forms.py]
    [admin.py]
    [urls.py] as AppUrls
    [tests.py]
    [load_sample_data.py]
  }

  database "SQLite database\n(db.sqlite3)" as DB
  folder "templates/" as Templates
  folder "static/glossary/\nCSS + Vue enhancements" as Static
  folder "docs/" as Docs
}

User --> Project : HTTP request
Project --> AppUrls : route app URLs
AppUrls --> [views.py]
[views.py] --> [forms.py]
[views.py] --> [models.py]
[admin.py] --> [models.py]
[models.py] --> DB
[views.py] --> Templates : render HTML
Templates --> Static : CSS
[load_sample_data.py] --> [models.py] : demo data
[tests.py] --> App : workflow tests

note bottom of App
The prototype is intentionally server-rendered
with Django templates, plain CSS and small
Vue components for progressive enhancement.
end note

@enduml
